5:
Phew... We've been at this for a while
now! Got ourselves a nice haul.
11:
In that case, let's just go get
something to eat!
15:
Don't tell me... SoyMate again? It's so
uncannyâ€”food whose flavor
changes on a whim... I can't get
used to it.
23: Gah. Get the hell out of our way!
27:
Running IS your best bet... but it
seems you weren't fast enough.
30:
Shit. It's 3MM! How'd they get here so
fast...
32:
It's in the name. We get to the crime
scene in three minutes or less.
35:
Now would be the time to
surrenderâ€”before things get worse
for you.
38:
No way! We're not gonna let
ourselves be taken in that easily!
40:
What a shame. For your sakes, I was
hoping you'd go quietly.
Surround them, men! Don't let them
escape!
55:
So, you're from 3MM Security. I have
to commend your teamwork; your
unit moved as one.
59:
Thank you. I could say the same of
you. You're so good, I have a hard
time believing you're actually
Organics.
63:
The name's Carbina, I'm a squad
commander in 3MM. Thank you for
aiding me in my missionâ€”
68:
From HQ?
Excuse me, I need to get this.
85:
Anyway, I was hoping to thank you
for your help. Are you free right now?
I'd like to treat you to a meal.
89: Oh my! This is quite... sweet!
93:
I'm somewhat of a foodie. I
specialize in budget restaurants
around here. I tend to know the
places that serve the best AdTaste.
98:
Budget AdTaste? I didn't know there
was such a thing.
101:
Really? That's odd. It's only available
in this neighborhood, so it's pretty
popular with the locals.
103:
You must not be from around here.
I'd suspected as much, given your
clothes.
107:
...Sounds like you already had your
suspicions.
111:
You've got a talking mutant with
you. You did a half-decent job of
hiding your identities, but not good
enough.
113:
I'd recommend being more wary of
these sorts of things. You're rather
well-known around these parts.
116:
Seriously? When did we become
celebrities?
120:
Around the time when someone
blew a hole in the roof. And then
when that automaton went on a
rampage.
122:
As well as some other incidents
which you're presumed to be
involved in. Do you want to hear a
list?
126:
I'm not sure how I feel about this...
We're being tracked almost as if
we're suspects in a crime.
129: The jury's still out on that. In fact...
132:
My assignment was to make
contact with you and find out who
you really are. Sniff out your motives,
grasp your movements, that kind of
stuff.
134:
Before you ask, I've already located
your safe house.
137:
Not much activity over there. That
leads me to assume it's not your
primary base of operations.
141:
Uh... I have the right to remain silent?
...I think?
144:
That's all the answer I needed. You're
an honest bunchâ€”maybe to a fault.
147:
Regardless, there's no need to worry.
I won't reveal this to my company.
153:
Because they didn't tell me NOT to
hide it.
156:
You aren't bad people. And
therefore, you aren't my enemies.
160:
And to be honest, I'm rather curious
about you. I was hoping you'd take
me along with you.
163:
You know, given everything you just
said, that sounds kiiind of like
blackmail.
167:
But, then again, I don't think you're
that kind of person either.
170:
Even if you do submit a report to
your bosses, I hope you're careful
about what you write.
179:
To think that such a device existed
under DAN the whole time. How
could they keep something this big
hidden for so long? This has
implications for all of Noxel...
182:
I suppose I'll have to carefully
choose what information I pass
along.
185:
Yeah. We've got a lot of people who
do the same. They keep the details
secret. Do you think you can do the
same?
189: ...Yes. I think I can manage that.
193:
Looks like you're a bigger deal than I
initially gave you credit for.
Fascinating.
196:
All right then. I, Carbina, squad
commander of 3MM, will see for
myself what you're really made of,
Alk.
199:
Let's see what this brave new world
has to offer.
